HEADWORD: Hounding
<hw>Hound"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of one who
hounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>The part of a mast below the
hounds and above the deck.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hound's-tongue</ent>⟦br⟧
